Very enjoyable and I think it hits the sweet spot in terms of difficulty.

1. Took me about 10 seconds to get it
2. 8 mins. It took me more than I'd like to admit to handle the "X" properly.

Typescript:
```
const N: number = parseInt(readline());

const order = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 0];
const empty = Array(N * 2 + 1)
  .fill("*")
  .join("");

console.log(empty);

let index = 0;
for (; index < order.length; ) {
  let line = "*";
  for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {
    const char = order[index++];
    line += `${char != null ? char : "X"}*`;
  }
  console.log(line);
  console.log(empty);
}
```
